                "alt": "Sharing food"
              }
            }]
          }]
        },
        {
          "id": "body-3",
          "type": "row",
          "columns": [{
            "id": "col-7",
            "style": { "backgroundColor": "transparent", "padding": "0 34px 30px 34px" },
            "contents": [{
              "type": "text",
              "content": {
                "html": "<p style=\"color:#3b332d;line-height:1.9;margin:0 0 22px 0;\">Food doesn’t fix everything. It doesn’t erase history or difference. But it gives people a reason to be in the same room. It turns a stranger into someone whose food you want to try again.</p><p style=\"color:#3b332d;line-height:1.9;margin:0;\">That’s the part that sticks. A good meal isn’t just flavors. It’s a memory of who you ate it with.</p>"
              }
            }]
          }]
